---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Shingai Thornton">
  <div class="space-y-6">
    <p class="text-stone-700 leading-relaxed max-w-md">
      Building <a href="https://halcyonic.systems" style="color: #0d9488; text-decoration-color: rgba(13,148,136,0.3);" class="hover:opacity-80">Halcyonic Systems</a>, a research organization focused on formal systems modeling — being precise about how complex systems actually work.
    </p>
    <p class="text-stone-700 leading-relaxed max-w-md">
      <span style="font-variant: small-caps; letter-spacing: 0.05em;">Previously</span> political economy, then crypto — both were going to make the world better. Then I stumbled across <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Systems_science">systems science</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Systems_theory#General_systems_research_and_systems_inquiry">general systems research</a>, which seemed to offer a shared formal foundation for reasoning rigorously about complex systems across domains. Except systems science itself turned out to be fragmented, with no integrated usable science to speak of. So now I work on that.
    </p>
    <p class="now-line max-w-md">
      Currently: building a backyard bee observatory with a Raspberry Pi; reading <a href="https://categoricalfuture.com/" style="color: #6b5361;">A Categorical Defense of Our Future</a>.
    </p>
    <div class="pt-2">
      <a href="/archive" class="text-sm hover:text-stone-900 arrow-link" style="color: #a3856a;">Writing, 2019–2023 <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
